The function is using properties of the function object instead of defining global variables to hold its state.

The assignments at the end just initialize the `modules` and `payloads` properties. Otherwise, the function would have to check for this every time, with something like:

```
if (!define.modules) {
    define.modules = {};
    define.payloads = {};
}
```
before the code that adds the new entries to those objects. But since this only needs to be done one, it&#39;s wasteful to check it every time.

